{
  "texts": [
    "Here are some prominent techniques: 1) Curriculum Learning: Curriculum Learning is a strategy that aims to effectively create domain-specific abilities in a model by progressively raising the complexity of the training data [5].",
    "2) Knowledge Distillation: Information distillation involves transferring information from a pre-trained model that is specialised to a certain domain to the LLM.",
    "This process may speed up learning and help overcome the problem of limited data availability.",
    "3) Data Augmentation: The process of creating artificial data that is relevant to a certain domain enhances the training dataset, resulting in a more resilient and adaptable model.",
    "4) These methods have clearly enhanced the efficiency of completing tasks in several fields, including medical diagnostics and financial forecasting."
  ]
}